1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a congestion control protocol for networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the estimation of flow rate and the use of feedback, which are concepts related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with stability analysis of a control protocol, which is a topic within this sub-category. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - Although not directly related, the use of feedback and optimization in the protocol design may have some connections to neural and evolutionary computing. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses the performance of the RCP protocol, which is a topic within this sub-category.
